 <text>
  <front>
   <head>AN ADDRESS TO NIGHT</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Hail solemn Night, ye glitt'ring lamps of Heav'n,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Fair orb of light, with mild benignant rays,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To my torn breast a woman's heart is given,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Or in soft numbers I'd attempt thy praise.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Then let me tell ye, silent spirits round,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Ye unseen beings, pure as breathing spring,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Who in my bosom plac'd this deadly wound,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">No viper's poison here, no serpent's sting.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Fair was the form, as mortal form can be,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Alas! I languish for no common swain;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Graceful the youth who gave this wound to me,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And yet I'm tortur'd, with uncommon pain.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">O thou Great Power! from whom I drew my breath,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">May I presume to beg an early grave;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To ask the awful previlege of death,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Forgive me, Heav'n! no other boon I crave.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
